{"id": 232040672, "title": "Monsoon onset takes place in Mumbai two days in advance", "text": "Mumbai woke up to showers of first spell of monsoon rains on Sunday as the southwest monsoon arrived two days ahead of usual date of onset in the city. Last year, the onset took place on June 24, two weeks later than the usual date. In Mumbai, monsoon onset usually takes place between June 8 and 11, and the India Meteorology Department (IMD) had predicted the onset to take place on June 11 this year. The IMD has issued a yellow alert indicating light to moderate spells of rain in Mumbai, Thane, Palghar districts till Tuesday. For Raigad, Ratnagiri and Sindhudurg districts, an orange alert has been issued for Monday and Tuesday. \"We have issued a yellow alert for June 10-11 since we are expecting heavy rain during these two days, which may be coupled with thunderstorms and gusty winds. At present, there is an upper air circulation which has made conditions for heavy rainfall,\" Sushma Nair, scientist from IMD Mumbai told Express on Sunday. The IMD's Santacruz observatory recorded 18.8 mm of rain during the last 24 hours, on Sunday, while the IMD's coastal observatory at Colaba recorded 8.8 mm of rain. According to the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation's (BMC) automatic weather systems (AWS), 17.99 mm of rains were recorded in western suburbs, 7.44 mm of rain in eastern suburbs and 3.92 mm of rains were recorded in the island city. From early morning, Mumbai's skyline got covered with dark clouds and the weather bureau officials said that cloudy sky will continue throughout the day. Meanwhile, the IMD's Santacruz observatory recorded a maximum temperature of 32.8 degrees, which was 1.2 degrees below normal, while the coastal observatory at Colaba recorded 30 degrees, which was 3.7 degrees below normal. The relative humidity stood at 68%. The monsoon onset took place in Kerala on May 30 following which it travelled to Maharashtra towards the north.", "summary": "", "url": "https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/mumbai/monsoon-onset-in-mumbai-two-days-in-advance-9381852/", "image": "https://images.indianexpress.com/2024/06/monsoon_a57dcf.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 15:28:05", "author": null, "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.124}